(September 22, 1960)

Concur — Botein, P. J., Breitel, Rabin. Valente and McNally, J.T.

In the Matter of the Estate of Harry Pasialis, Deceased. Paul Anayannis, Appellant; Public Administrator of the County of New York, as Administrator, et al., Respondents.

Motion to dismiss appeal granted, with *930$10 costs, unless the appellant procures the record on appeal and appellant’s points to be served and filed on or before October 4, 1960, with notice of argument for the November 1960 Term of this court, said appeal to be argued or submitted when reached.
